It appears from Virgil, and the other Roman writers, that Julius Caesar was of this royal race 3 and that Augustus was his sole heir. The natural result of all this is, that the promises made to the Roman people, in and through this race, terminating in Augus- tus; the Romans, if they would obey the gods, and be masters of the world, were to yield obedience to the new establishment under that prinee.
